      <h1 class='title'>Official Report of the Northern Ireland Orders Grand Committee</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 13 December 2004 vol 667 cc1-14GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1gc' title='Col. 1GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 December 2004 vol 667 c1GC' name='column_1gc' href='#column_1gc' rel='bookmark'>1GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0667P0-05279'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_1' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="italic">Monday, 13 December 2004.</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0667P0-05280'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_2' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="bold">The Committee met at half past three of the clock.</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0667P0-05281'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_3' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [The DEPUTY CHAIRMAN OF COMMITTEES (Viscount Allenby of Megiddo) in the Chair.]
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0667P0-05282'>
        <a name='S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_4'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-michael-allenby' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_4' title='Link to this speech by Mr Michael Allenby' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-michael-allenby" title="Mr Michael Allenby">The Deputy Chairman of Committees (Viscount Allenby of Megiddo)</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Before the Minister moves that the first order be considered, it may be helpful to say a word about the procedure for today's Grand Committee. Our proceedings are essentially the same as those of the House. Noble Lords will speak standing; all noble Lords are free to attend and participate; and the proceedings will be reported in <span class="italic">Hansard</span> in the usual way.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0667P0-05283'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_5' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        As we are in Committee, Members may speak more than once on any Motion.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0667P0-05284'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_6' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        I should, however, make it clear to noble Lords that this Committee is charged only to consider orders, not to approve or not approve them. The Motion to approve will be moved in the Chamber in the usual way.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0667P0-05285'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041213_GCR_7' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The main difference between our proceedings and the proceedings on the Floor of the House is that the House has agreed that there shall be no Divisions in a Grand Committee. Any Motion on which agreement cannot be reached should be withdrawn.
      </p>
